title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a plan that loads waiting list data for the month “2025-05”, and only have waiting list type that contains the word “Aktiv”, for these compute an contain the waiting list total for each organisation where the total is larger than 10000. For these organisations, the plan must get the total number of moveouts from 2025 and return the organisation name, the total in aktiv waiting list in 2025-05 and total of move outs in 2025. Output should be in textfile.

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val ym = r.getField(2).toString; val wtype = r.getField(6).toString; ym == "2025-05" && wtype.contains("Aktiv") }

(t: ((Int, (Int, Int)), org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record)) => { val orgName = t._2.getField(3).toString; val waitingTotal = t._1._2._1; val moveouts = t._1._2._2; s"${orgName} | ${waitingTotal} | ${moveouts}" }

log.thoughts: Filter waiting lists for 2025-05 and 'Aktiv', aggregate per organisation, keep totals>10000, aggregate 2025 moveouts per organisation, join results with organisation names and write strings to a text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT waitinglist_id, organisation_id, year_month, year, month, date, waiting_list_type, total FROM factwaitinglists) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val ym = r.getField(2).toString; val wtype = r.getField(6).toString; ym == "2025-05" && wtype.contains("Aktiv") }

data.table: (SELECT moveout_id, organisation_id, department_id, tenancy_types_id, move_out_year, years_lived, sum_of_move_outs FROM factmoveouts) as X
(SELECT organisation_id, organisation_no, active_organisation, name, social_housing_org, municipality FROM organisation) as X

data.udf: (t: ((Int, (Int, Int)), org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record)) => { val orgName = t._2.getField(3).toString; val waitingTotal = t._1._2._1; val moveouts = t._1._2._2; s"${orgName} | ${waitingTotal} | ${moveouts}" }

title: Wayang: Wayang plan sent to Wayang
